            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/49383",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "There is a place to contribute a patch: https:\/\/github.com\/zendframework\/ZF2Package\r\n\r\nEach package has a file returning a list of dependencies -- for Zend_Validator, it's https:\/\/github.com\/zendframework\/ZF2Package\/blob\/master\/data\/dependencies\/Zend_Validator.php.\r\n\r\nObviously, you also need to trace each package on which a dependency is made to find which one may have the erroneous dependency. Also, if you think a given dependency is _optional_, versus _require_, you can change which array it is returned in (or introduce the \"optional\" array, if none present).",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-12-27T21:16:14.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-12-27T21:16:14.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/49385",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=evan.pro",
                        "name": "evan.pro",
                        "displayName": "Evan Coury",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "The actual problem is the Zend_Json package which has an optional dependency on Zend_Server. I'll take a closer look in a bit.\r\n\r\nhttps:\/\/github.com\/zendframework\/ZF2Package\/blob\/2e5d629535c724c1b7aed06c24a249948b584b1e\/data\/dependencies\/Zend_Json.php",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=evan.pro",
                        "name": "evan.pro",
                        "displayName": "Evan Coury",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-12-28T01:51:03.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-12-28T01:51:03.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/49446",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=alganet",
                        "name": "alganet",
                        "displayName": "Alexandre Gomes Gaigalas",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "The problem seems to be in the Zend_Json package indeed, Evan.\r\n\r\nI'm actually creating a package which optionally depends on Zend_Validator. Declaring the optional dependency on package.xml and installing with -o also installs every optional dependency recursively (all the optional dependency tree from Zend_Validator).\r\n\r\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=alganet",
                        "name": "alganet",
                        "displayName": "Alexandre Gomes Gaigalas",
